definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  inositol phosphate(n) + H2O -eq- inositol phosphate(n-1) + phosphate. This reaction is the removal of a phosphate group from an inositol phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  sinapaldehyde + NADPH + H+ -eq- sinapyl-alcohol + NADP+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  baicalin + H2O -eq- baicalein + D-glucuronate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  beta-D-glucose 6-phosphate + coenzyme F420 + H+ -eq- 6-O-phosphono-D-glucono-1,5-lactone + reduced coenzyme F420.
Catalysis of the reaction -  reactive black 5 + hydrogen peroxide -eq- oxidized reactive black 5 + 2 H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GDP-mannose + H2O -eq- GMP + mannose-1-phosphate.

label.value: reduced coenzyme F420 - heterodisulfide oxidoreductase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  reduced coenzyme F420 + CoB-S-S-CoM -eq- coenzyme F420 + CoM-SH + CoB-SH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  propan-2-ol + coenzyme F420 -eq- acetone + reduced coenzyme F420.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GTP + factor gamma-F420-2 + H+ -eq- coenzyme F390-G + diphosphate.

label.value: reduced coenzyme F420 - quinone oxidoreductase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  reduced coenzyme F420 + 2,3-dimethyl-1,4-naphthoquinone -eq- coenzyme F420 + reduced 2,3-dimethyl-1,4-naphthoquinone. Reduced 2,3-dimethyl-1,4-naphthoquinone is also known as 2,3-dimethyl-1,4-hydronaphthoquinone.

Catalysis of the reaction -  chitobiose + phosphate -eq- N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine 1-phosphate. This reaction is the phosphorolysis of chitobiose, (GlcNAc)2, a dimer of beta-(1--gt-4) linked glucosamine units.

Catalysis of the hydrolysis of hexosaminic linkages in chondroitin, a linear polymer structure composed of the repeating disaccharide unit [--gt-4)-D-glucuronic acid-(1--gt-3)-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine-(1-], also written as [--gt-4GlcUA1--gt-3GalNAc1-].
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,4,6-trinitrophenol + H- -eq- 2,4,6-trinitrophenol hydride Meisenheimer complex. Coenzyme F420 supplies the hydride (H-) in the reaction.
Catalysis of the reaction -  trinitrophenol hydride Meisenheimer complex + H- -eq- trinitrophenol dihydride Meisenheimer complex (aci form). Coenzyme F420 supplies the hydride (H-) in the reaction.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,4-dinitrophenol + H- -eq- 2,4-dinitrophenol hydride Meisenheimer complex. Coenzyme F420 supplies the hydride (H-) in the reaction.

Catalysis of the reaction -  [beta-(1--gt-4)-D-glucosamine]n-[N-acetyl-D-glucosamine]m -eq- D-glucosamine + [beta-(1--gt-4)-D-glucosamine](n-1)-[N-acetyl-D-glucosamine]m. This reaction is the hydrolysis of chitosan or chitosan oligosaccharides to remove a D-glucosamine residue from the non-reducing termini -  chitosan is a linear polysaccharide composed of randomly distributed beta-(1--gt-4)-linked D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine units.

Catalysis of the reaction -  gellan -eq- n beta-D-4-deoxy-delta4,5-GlcAp-(1--gt-4)-beta-D-Glcp-(1--gt-4)-alpha-L-Rhap-(1--gt-3)-beta-D-Glcp. This reaction is the eliminative cleavage of beta-D-glucopyranosyl-(1--gt-4)-beta-D-glucopyranosyluronate bonds of gellan backbone, releasing tetrasaccharides containing a 4-deoxy-4,5-unsaturated D-glucopyranosyluronic acid at the non-reducing end -  in the product, the abbreviations are D-glucose (Glc), D-glucuronic acid (GlcA), and L-rhamnose (Rha).

Catalysis of the cleavage of a carbon-oxygen bond in ulvan, a carbohydrate composed of a repeating structure of [--gt-4)-beta-D-GlcA-(1,4)-alpha-L-Rha 3S-(1--gt-4)-alpha-L-IdoA-(1--gt-4)-alpha-L-Rha 3S-(1-]n. Continued digest of ulvan with an enzyme that can catalyze this reaction results in ulvanobiouronic acid A 3-sulfate [--gt-4)-beta-D-GlcpA-(1--gt-4)-alpha-L-Rhap 3-sulfate-(1-]n with 4-deoxy-L-threo-hex-4-enopyranosiduronic acid at the non-reducing end.

Catalysis of the cleavage of glycosidic bonds through a beta-elimination reaction on alginate, a linear polysaccharide consisting of guluronate (G) and mannuronate (M) as the monomer constituents. An oligoalginate is a linear polymer of two, three or four units of (1--gt-4)-alpha-L-guluronic acid and beta-D-mannuronic acid, releasing monosaccharides with 4-deoxy-alpha-L-erythro-hex-4-enopyranuronosyl groups at their ends.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2 reduced coenzyme F420 + O2 -eq- 2 coenzyme F420 + 2 H2O.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the alpha-(1--gt-4) linkage of the terminal, non-reducing alpha-D-mannose residues in alpha-D-mannosides.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the alpha-(1--gt-6) bonds of alpha-D-mannose residues in mannosyl-oligosaccharide.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the alpha-(1--gt-3) bonds of alpha-D-mannose residues in mannosyl-oligosaccharide.
Catalysis of the glycosidic cleavage of the terminal 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranoside 6-sulfate (6-SO3-GlcNAc) residue from sulfomucin, a sulfated mucin derivative.
Catalysis of the reaction -  coenzyme F390-A -eq- AMP + coenzyme F420.
Catalysis of the reaction -  coenzyme F390-G -eq- GMP + coenzyme F420.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of brefeldin A to produce brefeldin A acid. Brefeldin A is also known as gamma,4-dihydroxy-2-(6-hydroxy-1-heptenyl)-4-cyclopentanecrotonic acid lambda-lactone.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N,N'-diacetylchitobiose (GlcNac2) + H2O -eq- acetate + 2-acetamido-4-O-(2-amino-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranosyl)-2-deoxy-D-glucose (GlcN-GlcNAc).
Catalysis of the reaction -  glucosyl-N-acetylglucosamine + H2O -eq- glucosamine + N-acetylglucosamine.

Catalysis of the reaction -  R1-L-rhamnose-(1--gt-3)-alpha-L-rhamnose-R2 + H2O -eq- R1-L-rhamnose + L-rhamnose-R2. This reaction is the hydrolysis of an alpha-(1--gt-3) linkage between two rhamnose residues in a polysaccharide chain.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the glycosidic bond in an unsaturated saccharide between the unsaturated glucuronyl residue at the nonreducing terminus and the saccharide linked to the residue.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1--gt-3)-beta-D-mannosidic linkages in mannans, releasing mannose.

Catalysis of the reaction -  chitooligosaccharide with N-acetylglucosamine at nonreducing terminal + H2O -eq- chitooligosaccharide with glucosamine at nonreducing terminal + acetate. This reaction is the deacetylation of a chitooligosaccharide at the nonreducing N-acetylglucosamine residue -  chitooligosaccharide are composed of (1--gt-4)-linked D-glucosamine (GlcN) and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine (GlcNAc) in varying proportions.

Catalysis of the reaction -  (2-keto-3-deoxynononic acid)n + H2O -eq- (2-keto-3-deoxynononic acid)n-1 + 2-keto-3-deoxynononic acid. This reaction is the hydrolysis of a 2-keto-3-deoxynononic acid residue from a poly-2-keto-3-deoxynononic acid chain.

Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of xylogalacturonate by cleavage of the alpha-(1,4)-linkage. Xylogalacturonate (XGA) is composed of a chain of alpha-(1,4)-linked D-galacturonic acid residues with beta-D-xylose substituted at the O3 position.
Catalysis of the reaction -  pectin + H2O -eq- pectate + acetate. This reaction is the hydrolysis of acetyl esters of pectin, producing pectate, partially esterified pectin.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of alpha-(2--gt-3)-glycosidic linkages of terminal sialic residues in substrates.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of alpha-(2--gt-6)-glycosidic linkages of terminal sialic residues in substrates.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of alpha-(2--gt-8)-glycosidic linkages of terminal sialic residues in substrates.

Catalysis of the reaction -  [X]-4-O-methyl-D-glucuronic acid + H2O -eq- [X]-OH + methyl-D-glucuronic acid. This reaction is the hydrolysis of the ester linkage between 4-O-methyl-D-glucuronic acid (MeGlcA) and an alcohol (-OH) group attached to a molecule, denoted here as [X].
Catalysis of the transfer of sialyl residues alpha-2,3-linked to a beta galactosyl residue on the donor to form an alpha-2,3 linkage to a terminal beta galactosyl residue on the acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  sulfite + 3 1,5-dihydrocoenzyme F420 -eq- hydrogen sulfide + 3 H2O + 3 coenzyme F420. 1,5-dihydrocoenzyme F420 is also known as reduced coenzyme F420.
Catalysis of the reaction -  aflatoxin + 1,5-dihydrocoenzyme F420 -eq- aflatoxin with reduced furanocoumarin moiety + coenzyme F420. 1,5-dihydrocoenzyme F420 is also known as reduced coenzyme F420.

label.value: reduced coenzyme F420 - NADP+ oxidoreductase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  NADP+ + 1,5-dihydrocoenzyme F420 -eq- NADPH + H+ + coenzyme F420. 1,5-dihydrocoenzyme F420 is also known as reduced coenzyme F420.

Catalysis of the cleavage of a carbon-oxygen bond in acharan sulfate, a glycosaminoglycan with a uniformly repeating disaccharide structure of alpha-D-N-acetylglucosaminyl-2-O-sulfo-alpha-L-iduronic acid.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol + ATP -eq- a 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 5-phosphate + ADP + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  a 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4-phosphate + ATP -eq- a 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4-bisphosphate + ADP + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4-bisphosphate + ATP -eq- a 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4,5-trisphosphate + ADP + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + a phosphatidylinositol bisphosphate -eq- ADP + a phosphatidylinositol trisphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a medium-chain aldehyde + NAD+ -eq- a medium-chain carboxylate + NADH + H+. Medium-chain aldehydes have a chain length of between 8 and 12 carbons.
